obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `The Deo Estate Act, 1886`
  line `A CT N O. IX OF 18 86.`
  line `P ASSED BY THE G OVERNOR G ENERAL OF I NDIA IN C OUNCIL.`
  line `(Received the assent of the Governor General on the 10 th March,1886.)`
  line `An Act to apply the Chutia Nagpur Encumbered Estates Act, 1876, to the Deo Estate in the`
  line `Gaya District.`
  line `W HEREAS Raja Bhikam Narayan Singh Bahadur, of Deo in the district of Gaya, is subject to,`
  line `and his immoveable property is charged with, debts and liabilities other than debts due, and`
  line `liabilities in - curred, to the Government;`
  line `And whereas the said Raja h as requested that the provisions of the Chutia Nagpur Encumbered`
  line `Estates Act,1876, be applied to his case;`
  line `And whereas the persons to whom the debts are due and the liabilities have been incurred have`
  line `assented to the applica tion of the Chutia Nagpur Encumbered Estates Act, 1876 (VI of 1876.), to`
  line `the case on the condition that their title to receive the principal and interest due to them be in no`
  line `way impaired thereby;`
  line `It is hereby enacted as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title and commencement. — (1) This Act may be called the Deo Estate Act, 1886; and`
  line `(2) It shall come into force at once.`
  line `2. Application of Act VI of 1876 to the Deo Estate. — The provisions of the Chutia Nagpur`
  line `Encumbered Estates Act,1876 (VI of 1876), as amended b y Act V of 1884, may be applied to the`
  line `case of the said Raja Bhikam Narayan Singh Bahadur, subject to the following modifications,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `(1) The expressions “Commissioner”, “De puty Commissioner” and “holder”, where used in the`
  line `said Act, shall be construed as referring to the Commissioner of the Patna division, the Collector of`
  line `the Gaya district and the said Ra ’ j a ’, respectively.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything in section 2 of the said Act, the Commissioner may, without any`
  line `further application from the said Ra ’ ja ’ and without any further notification of the consent of the`
  line `Lieutenant - Governor of Bengal, publish an order under that section appointing a manager and`
  line `vesting in him the management of the whole of the im moveable property of or to which the said`
  line `Ra ’ ja ’ is then possessed or entitled in his own right, or which he is entitled to redeem, or which`
  line `may be acquired by or devolve on him or his heir during the continuance of the management.`
  line `(3) Section 4 of the sai d Act shall be read as if after t he words “and their families” the words`
  line `“and persons entitled to receive maintenance from the property” were added.`
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything in section 8 –`
  line `the sums mentioned in column 2 and column 4 of the sc hedule to this Act, as principal and as`
  line `balance due from the said Raja on the thirty - first day of December, 1885, respectively,`
  line `and the rate of interest mentioned in column 3 of that schedule,`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-2
  sectionNo (2)
