  title `Page 2`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  sourcePage 2
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `shall, save in so far as any error with respect thereto may be proved to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Commissioner, be deemed to be justly due to the several persons mentioned in column 1 of the`
  line schedule.
  line `(5) The scheme prepared and approve under section 11 of the said Act shall provide that out of`
  line `the residue applicable under section 4 of that Act, after discharge of costs of management, to the`
  line `settlement of debts and liabilities, interest at the rate of six per cent. per annum in respect of so`
  line `much of the principal sum of six hundred and fifty thousand rupees as is for the tim e being due to`
  line `the M aharaja of Darbhanga shall be paid to the Maharaja before any sum is paid thereout to any`
  line `other creditor.`
  line `(6) The second clause of section 12 of the said Act shall be read as if for the words “ at any`
  line `time before a scheme has been app roved by him under section 11” the words “ at any time before`
  line `the occurrence of either of the events mentioned in the first and third clauses of this section” were`
  line substituted.
  line `(7) The power conferred on the manager by the second clause of section 16 of t he said Act, to`
  line `apply for the removal of a mortgagee or conditional vendee in possession, shall not be exercised.`
  line `(8) The exercise of the power of sale conferred by section 18 of the said Act shall be subject to`
  line `the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `(a) th at one month’s notice shall be given to the Maharaja of Darbhanga of the manager’s`
  line `intention to sell any property of which the said Maharaja is mortgagee;`
  line `(b) that until the debt due to the said Maharaja has been reduced to the sum of six hundred`
  line `and fifty thousand rupees no portion of the proceeds of the sale of any of that property shall,`
  line `without the previous consent of the Maharaja, be paid to any other cre ditor; and`
  line `(c) that, except with the previous consent of the said Maharaja, so much of that property`
  line `shall be left unsold as will yield a yearly income sufficient, after compliance with the rest of the`
  line `scheme prepared and approved under section 11 of the said Act, to meet the yearly interest for`
  line `the time being payable to the Maharaja.`
  line `(9) Section 23 of the said Act shall be read as if for the words “ the Courts in Chutia Nagpur”`
  line `the words “any Court “ were substituted, and as if the following words wer e added to the section`
  line `to the section, namely: —`
  line `“and a suit relating to a claim of maintenance from the property shall not be entertained by`
  line `an y such Court without the previous consent of the Commissioner.”`
  line `3. Saving of Priority of Crown debts. — Nothing contained in this Act shall be construed as`
  line `affecting the priority of any debt due, or liability incurred, to the Government.`
  line ______
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
